Available Tools: get_historical_readings | get_average_reading | get_min_max | export_sensor_data
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "sensor_id": "string", "from": "string", "to": "string", "interval": "string" }
Response Schema: { "sensor_id": "string", "readings": [{ "timestamp": "string", "value": number }], "avg": number, "min": number, "max": number }
---
Question: Pull the hourly radiation levels for sensor RAD-004 in the nuclear lab from 6 AM to 6 PM yesterday.
Call: { "func_call": "get_historical_readings", "sensor_id": "RAD-004", "from": "2023-11-01T06:00:00Z", "to": "2023-11-01T18:00:00Z", "interval": "hourly" }
Response: { "sensor_id": "RAD-004", "readings": [{ "timestamp": "2023-11-01T06:00:00Z", "value": 0.12 }, { "timestamp": "2023-11-01T09:00:00Z", "value": 0.14 }, { "timestamp": "2023-11-01T12:00:00Z", "value": 0.13 }, { "timestamp": "2023-11-01T15:00:00Z", "value": 0.15 }, { "timestamp": "2023-11-01T18:00:00Z", "value": 0.11 }], "avg": 0.13, "min": 0.11, "max": 0.15 }

